Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

To follow up on your earlier question in #openstack-infra about the Tempest test errors you're seeing here, it looks like your proposed change is consistently causing that particular Glance exercise in Tempest to no longer work (it hangs for around 180 minutes and then eventually gets killed by the build timeout).

Patch Set 6:

Hey Jeremy,

Thanks for getting back on that. 

It would be useful to know what is actually happening since tempests is not saying anything useful. Notice that the same test succeeded using the json interface, plus, tests doesn't fail always at the same point (see previous failures). I don't think this something being caused directly by this patch since it has succeeded before and the only thing that was done since the last success is a rebase. I could be wrong, though.

Pls, If you've any extra information about what could be happening, let me know.

Cheers,

Patch Set 6:

I'm not really familiar with what tempest is doing to exercise glance such that these failures appear (I'm just helping maintain the servers on which it runs). Is it possible you rebased this patch at a time when there were subtle bugs present in glance which were later fixed, and that after another rebase this might start working again?
